13.1.1   AC_MSG_CHECKING, AC_MSG_RESULT
=======================================
 
<<AC_MSG_CHECKING(<msg>)
  ...
  AC_MSG_RESULT(<msg>)
>>
  The `AC_MSG_CHECKING' function output message of the form `---
Checking <msg>... ' without any trailing newline. After the test
advertized by `AC_MSG_CHECKING' is performed, the `AC_MSG_RESULT'
function should be used to output the result.
  In certain cases users may want to redefine these function --- for
example, to use a different output formatting and/or to copy the
messages to a log file.
  Example: 
<<static. =
     AC_MSG_CHECKING(which foo to use)
     foo = ...
     AC_MSG_RESULT($(foo))
>>

