13.1.3   AC_MSG_YES_NO, AC_MSG_FOUND
====================================
 
<<flag = $(AC_MSG_YES_NO <bool expr>
  flag = $(AC_MSG_FOUND <bool expr>
>>
  
  The `AC_MSG_FOUND' function expects to receive a boolean flag
describing whether a test previously announced using the
`AC_MSG_CHECKING function found what it was looking for. `AC_MSG_FOUND'
will output the appropriate result ("found" or "NOT found") using the
`AC_MSG_RESULT function and return its argument back.
  The `AC_MSG_YES_NO' function is similar, outputting a simple ("yes" or
"NO"). 

